				\begin{document}$$\begin{aligned}^{{1}} {\text{D }} = & \, 0.{\text{2138C }} + { 3}.{9893 }\left( {{\text{r }} = \, 0.{9999}} \right){\text{ for ATO at 384 nm}} \\^{{1}} {\text{D }} = & \, 0.{48}0{\text{6C }} - \, 0.{9123 }\left( {{\text{r }} = \, 0.{9998}} \right){\text{ for ASP at 365 nm}}, \\ \end{aligned}$$\end{document}where 1D represents FDSFS peak amplitude, C is the drug concentration in μg/mL, and r is the correlation coefficient. This indicates that the calibration graphs are linear, as detailed in Table 1.

Following ICH guidelines, the LOD and LOQ were determined using the following formulas:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
